Diagnosis. This species is characterized by its relatively large size ( 11–13 mm ), characteristically spotted fore wings and the presence of tufts of stiff setae on the head ventrolaterally and on the fore femur ventrally. It is readily recognized using the characters given in the original description and figures (
ISHIKAWA & YANO 1999
).
